## 4. Non-Functional Requirements
### 4.1 UX & Accessibility (Conceptual)
- NFR-UX-001: Pages and navigation must be keyboard-navigable and screen-reader friendly.
- NFR-UX-002: Avatar and profile elements must expose appropriate labels/alt text.
- NFR-UX-003: Error states and empty states must be clearly communicated.

### 4.2 Privacy & Safety
- NFR-PRIV-001: Profile fields exposed publicly must be clearly distinguished from private/account-only fields.
- NFR-PRIV-002: Avatar and profile content must adhere to content policies (enforcement details are a separate moderation task).
- NFR-PRIV-003: Settings must not accidentally reveal sensitive information (e.g., emails) without explicit user choice.

### 4.3 Performance & Reliability
- NFR-PERF-001: Profile and settings pages should load within acceptable performance budgets (exact metrics to be defined by engineering).
- NFR-PERF-002: Avatar images should be delivered via the existing media pipeline (caching/CDN already covered at infra level).

