## 7. Owners Required
- Product/PM (you) — define priorities and fields, approve scope.
- Tech Lead — determine data model boundaries and service ownership for profile/settings.
- Backend engineer — implement persistence for profile/settings and avatar references.
- Frontend engineer — implement profile, settings, layout, and navigation UIs.
- UI/UX — finalize layout pattern (header/nav) and profile/settings visual hierarchy.
- Security/Compliance — sign off on what profile data is public vs private.

---

## 8. Risks & Mitigations
| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|--------|------------|
| Over-scoping profile fields for MVP | Delays and more complex forms | Start with small set of fields, iterate later. |
| Confusion between public vs private data | Privacy concerns or user mistrust | Clear labels and separation between profile and settings. |
| Navigation pattern changes later | Rework in layout and routes | Choose a simple, extensible pattern and document assumptions. |

